<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="766" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1996</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-05T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1771. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 354. Your 353, Embassy 1985, October 23, 6 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d766fn1">Not printed.</note> You are authorized
                                informally to discuss with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_VJ1">Ventosa</persName> the matter
                                of lifting cotton and petroleum and the imposition of bunker control
                                to insure regular service between Spain and the United States. It is
                                important <pb facs="0880" n="1714" xml:id="pg_1714"/> that your
                                conversation be entirely informal in character and designed to
                                ascertain the attitude of the Spanish Government without however
                                committing ourselves to any definite policy or implying that our
                                right to impose bunker control is in any way dependent on Spanish
                                acquiescence.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>